FIRST NAT. BANK OF PLAINFIELD, Appellant, v. CARRINGTON et al., Respondents. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. October 13, 1893.) Action by the First National Bank of Plainfield against Augustus B. Carrington and others.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and FOLLETT and PARKER, JJ.

H. Y. Stillman, for appellant. C. B. Pierce, for respondent Carrington. C. C. Keeler, for respondent Darrah.

Judgment reversed and new trial ordered, with costs to the appellant to abide event. Opinion by VAN BRUNT, P. J., withheld from publication by direction of the court.
